{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm going to speak"},{"time":2000,"text":"about a tiny, little idea."},{"time":5000,"text":"And this is about shifting baseline."},{"time":9000,"text":"And because the idea can be explained in one minute,"},{"time":13000,"text":"I will tell you three stories before"},{"time":16000,"text":"to fill in the time."},{"time":18000,"text":"And the first story"},{"time":20000,"text":"is about Charles Darwin, one of my heroes."},{"time":23000,"text":"And he was here, as you well know, in '35."},{"time":26000,"text":"And you'd think he was chasing finches,"},{"time":28000,"text":"but he wasn't."},{"time":30000,"text":"He was actually collecting fish."},{"time":32000,"text":"And he described one of them"},{"time":34000,"text":"as very \"common.\""},{"time":36000,"text":"This was the sailfin grouper."},{"time":38000,"text":"A big fishery was run on it"},{"time":40000,"text":"until the '80s."},{"time":43000,"text":"Now the fish is on the IUCN Red List."},{"time":46000,"text":"Now this story,"},{"time":48000,"text":"we have heard it lots of times"},{"time":51000,"text":"on Galapagos and other places,"},{"time":53000,"text":"so there is nothing particular about it."},{"time":56000,"text":"But the point is, we still come to Galapagos."},{"time":59000,"text":"We still think it is pristine."},{"time":62000,"text":"The brochures still say"},{"time":65000,"text":"it is untouched."},{"time":67000,"text":"So what happens here?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":70000,"text":"The second story, also to illustrate another concept,"},{"time":73000,"text":"is called shifting waistline."},{"time":75000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":78000,"text":"Because I was there in '71,"},{"time":80000,"text":"studying a lagoon in West Africa."},{"time":82000,"text":"I was there because I grew up in Europe"},{"time":85000,"text":"and I wanted later to work in Africa."},{"time":87000,"text":"And I thought I could blend in."},{"time":89000,"text":"And I got a big sunburn,"},{"time":91000,"text":"and I was convinced that I was really not from there."},{"time":94000,"text":"This was my first sunburn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96000,"text":"And the lagoon"},{"time":99000,"text":"was surrounded by palm trees,"},{"time":101000,"text":"as you can see, and a few mangrove."},{"time":103000,"text":"And it had tilapia"},{"time":105000,"text":"about 20 centimeters,"},{"time":107000,"text":"a species of tilapia called blackchin tilapia."},{"time":109000,"text":"And the fisheries for this tilapia"},{"time":111000,"text":"sustained lots of fish and they had a good time"},{"time":114000,"text":"and they earned more than average"},{"time":116000,"text":"in Ghana."},{"time":118000,"text":"When I went there 27 years later,"},{"time":121000,"text":"the fish had shrunk to half of their size."},{"time":124000,"text":"They were maturing at five centimeters."},{"time":126000,"text":"They had been pushed genetically."},{"time":128000,"text":"There were still fishes."},{"time":130000,"text":"They were still kind of happy."},{"time":132000,"text":"And the fish also were happy to be there."},{"time":137000,"text":"So nothing has changed,"},{"time":139000,"text":"but everything has changed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"My third little story"},{"time":143000,"text":"is that I was an accomplice"},{"time":145000,"text":"in the introduction of trawling"},{"time":147000,"text":"in Southeast Asia."},{"time":149000,"text":"In the '70s -- well, beginning in the '60s --"},{"time":152000,"text":"Europe did lots of development projects."},{"time":155000,"text":"Fish development"},{"time":157000,"text":"meant imposing on countries"},{"time":159000,"text":"that had already 100,000 fishers"},{"time":162000,"text":"to impose on them industrial fishing."},{"time":165000,"text":"And this boat, quite ugly,"},{"time":167000,"text":"is called the Mutiara 4."},{"time":169000,"text":"And I went sailing on it,"},{"time":171000,"text":"and we did surveys"},{"time":174000,"text":"throughout the southern South China sea"},{"time":177000,"text":"and especially the Java Sea."},{"time":179000,"text":"And what we caught,"},{"time":181000,"text":"we didn't have words for it."},{"time":183000,"text":"What we caught, I know now,"},{"time":186000,"text":"is the bottom of the sea."},{"time":188000,"text":"And 90 percent of our catch"},{"time":190000,"text":"were sponges,"},{"time":192000,"text":"other animals that are fixed on the bottom."},{"time":195000,"text":"And actually most of the fish,"},{"time":197000,"text":"they are a little spot on the debris,"},{"time":199000,"text":"the piles of debris, were coral reef fish."},{"time":202000,"text":"Essentially the bottom of the sea came onto the deck"},{"time":204000,"text":"and then was thrown down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206000,"text":"And these pictures are extraordinary"},{"time":209000,"text":"because this transition is very rapid."},{"time":212000,"text":"Within a year, you do a survey"},{"time":215000,"text":"and then commercial fishing begins."},{"time":217000,"text":"The bottom is transformed"},{"time":219000,"text":"from, in this case, a hard bottom or soft coral"},{"time":222000,"text":"into a muddy mess."},{"time":225000,"text":"This is a dead turtle."},{"time":227000,"text":"They were not eaten, they were thrown away because they were dead."},{"time":230000,"text":"And one time we caught a live one."},{"time":232000,"text":"It was not drowned yet."},{"time":234000,"text":"And then they wanted to kill it because it was good to eat."},{"time":237000,"text":"This mountain of debris"},{"time":240000,"text":"is actually collected by fishers"},{"time":243000,"text":"every time they go"},{"time":245000,"text":"into an area that's never been fished."},{"time":247000,"text":"But it's not documented."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249000,"text":"We transform the world,"},{"time":251000,"text":"but we don't remember it."},{"time":253000,"text":"We adjust our baseline"},{"time":256000,"text":"to the new level,"},{"time":258000,"text":"and we don't recall what was there."},{"time":262000,"text":"If you generalize this,"},{"time":264000,"text":"something like this happens."},{"time":266000,"text":"You have on the y axis some good thing:"},{"time":269000,"text":"biodiversity, numbers of orca,"},{"time":272000,"text":"the greenness of your country, the water supply."},{"time":275000,"text":"And over time it changes --"},{"time":277000,"text":"it changes"},{"time":279000,"text":"because people do things, or naturally."},{"time":281000,"text":"Every generation"},{"time":283000,"text":"will use the images"},{"time":285000,"text":"that they got at the beginning of their conscious lives"},{"time":288000,"text":"as a standard"},{"time":290000,"text":"and will extrapolate forward."},{"time":292000,"text":"And the difference then,"},{"time":294000,"text":"they perceive as a loss."},{"time":296000,"text":"But they don't perceive what happened before as a loss."},{"time":299000,"text":"You can have a succession of changes."},{"time":301000,"text":"At the end you want to sustain"},{"time":304000,"text":"miserable leftovers."},{"time":307000,"text":"And that, to a large extent, is what we want to do now."},{"time":310000,"text":"We want to sustain things that are gone"},{"time":313000,"text":"or things that are not the way they were."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317000,"text":"Now one should think"},{"time":319000,"text":"this problem affected people"},{"time":321000,"text":"certainly when in predatory societies,"},{"time":325000,"text":"they killed animals"},{"time":327000,"text":"and they didn't know they had done so"},{"time":329000,"text":"after a few generations."},{"time":331000,"text":"Because, obviously,"},{"time":334000,"text":"an animal that is very abundant,"},{"time":339000,"text":"before it gets extinct,"},{"time":342000,"text":"it becomes rare."},{"time":345000,"text":"So you don't lose abundant animals."},{"time":348000,"text":"You always lose rare animals."},{"time":350000,"text":"And therefore they're not perceived"},{"time":352000,"text":"as a big loss."},{"time":354000,"text":"Over time,"},{"time":356000,"text":"we concentrate on large animals,"},{"time":358000,"text":"and in a sea that means the big fish."},{"time":360000,"text":"They become rarer because we fish them."},{"time":363000,"text":"Over time we have a few fish left"},{"time":365000,"text":"and we think this is the baseline."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368000,"text":"And the question is,"},{"time":370000,"text":"why do people accept this?"},{"time":375000,"text":"Well because they don't know that it was different."},{"time":378000,"text":"And in fact, lots of people, scientists,"},{"time":381000,"text":"will contest that it was really different."},{"time":383000,"text":"And they will contest this"},{"time":385000,"text":"because the evidence"},{"time":387000,"text":"presented in an earlier mode"},{"time":392000,"text":"is not in the way"},{"time":395000,"text":"they would like the evidence presented."},{"time":397000,"text":"For example,"},{"time":399000,"text":"the anecdote that some present,"},{"time":401000,"text":"as Captain so-and-so"},{"time":403000,"text":"observed lots of fish in this area"},{"time":406000,"text":"cannot be used"},{"time":408000,"text":"or is usually not utilized by fishery scientists,"},{"time":411000,"text":"because it's not \"scientific.\""},{"time":413000,"text":"So you have a situation"},{"time":415000,"text":"where people don't know the past,"},{"time":418000,"text":"even though we live in literate societies,"},{"time":421000,"text":"because they don't trust"},{"time":423000,"text":"the sources of the past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426000,"text":"And hence, the enormous role"},{"time":429000,"text":"that a marine protected area can play."},{"time":431000,"text":"Because with marine protected areas,"},{"time":434000,"text":"we actually recreate the past."},{"time":438000,"text":"We recreate the past that people cannot conceive"},{"time":441000,"text":"because the baseline has shifted"},{"time":443000,"text":"and is extremely low."},{"time":445000,"text":"That is for people"},{"time":447000,"text":"who can see a marine protected area"},{"time":452000,"text":"and who can benefit"},{"time":454000,"text":"from the insight that it provides,"},{"time":457000,"text":"which enables them to reset their baseline."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461000,"text":"How about the people who can't do that"},{"time":463000,"text":"because they have no access --"},{"time":465000,"text":"the people in the Midwest for example?"},{"time":468000,"text":"There I think"},{"time":470000,"text":"that the arts and film"},{"time":472000,"text":"can perhaps fill the gap,"},{"time":474000,"text":"and simulation."},{"time":476000,"text":"This is a simulation of Chesapeake Bay."},{"time":479000,"text":"There were gray whales in Chesapeake Bay a long time ago --"},{"time":481000,"text":"500 years ago."},{"time":483000,"text":"And you will have noticed that the hues and tones"},{"time":486000,"text":"are like \"Avatar.\""},{"time":488000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":490000,"text":"And if you think about \"Avatar,\""},{"time":492000,"text":"if you think of why people were so touched by it --"},{"time":495000,"text":"never mind the Pocahontas story --"},{"time":499000,"text":"why so touched by the imagery?"},{"time":503000,"text":"Because it evokes something"},{"time":506000,"text":"that in a sense has been lost."},{"time":508000,"text":"And so my recommendation,"},{"time":510000,"text":"it's the only one I will provide,"},{"time":512000,"text":"is for Cameron to do \"Avatar II\" underwater."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}